the enchanter cham spell use to just be play around spell, but because of the resist change it is broken and way overpowered.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cantatus>Cantatus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#333333>(1/7/03 10:51:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/face.gif height=103 width=50></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soultion</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>fallacy6666 said:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Before they changed the way magic resist worked charm would break pretty randomley, you just could not count on it at all. But now you can get rooted or blinded even if you have 150 mr. This works the same with charm once an enchanter lowers the magic resist to a mob it literly has no magic resist left to check and break the charm, making it so the cham will last the entire time just about every time. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not sure if you're posting from experience or not, but I can quite honestly say I haven't experienced the same.  The resist nerf didn't seem to effect my charm durations noticably at all.  Even with the Enchanter AA skill Total Domination 3 (which makes charms not break as frequently), I still have pets that will break in under 10 seconds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Noonie said:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Just thought id mention that raiding hasnt sucked for enchanters since velious really, the overwhelming majority of modern higher end content has adds to be mezzed or pets to be charmed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, I suppose each guild does things their own way, but generally after you have 2-3 Enchanters (depending on the zone) the rest are going to be sitting around.  A good Enchanter can keep 3 mobs locked down, a great one can keep 5.  If you have 3 Enchanters, that means you could reasonably lock down 8-15 mobs and how often do you have that many mobs that need to be mezzed?  Of course, you can also add Bards to that.<br>
<br>
I will admit though that Verant has added a few encounters with our class in mind, specifically the ring type events and ones where the boss mob will summon or spawn adds on you (like Terris Thule).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> edit: As for your mezzing is &quot;a real tough job&quot; comment, i need to lol at that as well. I played an enchanter to 50, and i currently play a 65 mage with elemental charm, ive worked in bot and have used my dinky little elemental mez with the few second duration to keep as many as 2 adds locked down at once, with few problems (unslowed too). The key is really a good healer. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, of course healing is the key, but when you only have one healer and multiple spawns, the healer can't heal everyone, especially not with 10 second CHs going.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If i can do it with few problems so can an enchanter with their runes slow and tash and vastly superior in duration mez spells<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, you're honestly getting a very small sampling.  The elementals in BoT don't hit as hard as some other mobs, and they don't summon.  They also aren't as resistant as some other mobs I've come along (yes, even with tash).  Also keep in mind that a Magician likely isn't going to have to mezz 2 or mobs just solely for the fact that there aren't that many around to mezz, but keep in mind with focus effect, you can also cast your mezz about 1 second faster than an Enchanter.<br>
<br>
And, as I've said before, the Runes aren't really there as an advantage, but as a necessary precaution.  Enchanters would be dropping like flies if they didn't have 1500dmg to protect the first since mezzing, tashing and slowing all cause <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>huge</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> aggro.  Of course, Arcane Rune (the 1500 one) doesn't last too long when you have a mob beating on you that can hit for over 600dmg.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to argue though that Enchanters are superior to Magicians in mezzing.  Of course they are, but that's the way it's supposed to be.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>LordGojirax said:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Crowd control on high end raids is done by Wizards with their ultra root, root parking mobs off to the side.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah, like I said, each guild has their own tactics.  Our alliance prefers to &quot;off-tank&quot; or &quot;split tank&quot; on adds.  Either one warrior will tank an add, or a group(s) will break off to kill it.  Works better than mezzing in a lot of people's minds b/c then you are clearing stuff faster.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Jaytee said:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> There is no point discussing this, its part of the enchanter class, we get a semi-gimped version that doesnt work in the elemental planes unfortunatly. But where we can use it its very powerful.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Have to say this is really crappy.  Magicians <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>should</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be able to mezz and charm in the elemental planes.  The spells should at least be usuable in more than BoT anyhow.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Targal said:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I care that 1 chanter, 1 druid, 1 cleric were able to take down a named mob in PoS that hits for 1200 damage and wiped 10 people who tried him moments before.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If they need to &quot;fix&quot; one thing with charm, it's that pets can be healed.  This would make it harder for people to use charmed pets to tank for them on stuff.  I'd except Dire Charm from this however.  Just my opinion as an Enchanter.<br>
<br>
This whole issue is sort of a dead horse at the moment I'd say, because unfortuantly (for some unbeknownst reason) Verant is no longer publically responding to the players. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
